{"id":"257145016_Fault_tolerance_in_bubble-sort_graph_networks","abstract":"The bubble-sort graph B\"n is one of the attractive underlying topologies for distributed systems. F\"B(n,k) (resp. f\"B(n,k)) is the minimum number of faulty nodes (resp. links) that make every (n-k)-dimensional sub-bubble-sort graph faulty in B\"n under node (resp. link) failure model. In this paper, we proved that F\"B(n,0)=f\"B(n,0)=1, F\"B(n,1)=f\"B(n,1)=n for n>=4, F\"B(n,2)@?f\"B(n,2)@?n(2n-3) for n>=6, F\"B(n,n-2)=n!/2 for n>=3, f\"B(n,n-2)=(n-1)n!/2 for n>=3, F\"B(n,n-1)=n! for n>=2, and F\"B(n,k)@?f\"B(n,k)@?@?(k+1)/2@?k!C\"k^n for n>=6 and 3@?k@?n-3.","authors":["Shiying Wang","Yuxing Yang"],"meta":["March 2012Theoretical Computer Science 421:62â€“69","DOI:10.1016/j.tcs.2011.11.016"],"references":["220462717_An_algorithm_for_disjoint_paths_in_bubble-sort_graphs","235246839_A_kind_of_conditional_fault_tolerance_of_alternating_group_graphs","223818998_Hamiltonian_laceability_of_bubble-sort_graphs_with_edge_faults","223565276_How_robust_is_the_n-cube","223005863_Embedding_longest_fault-free_paths_onto_star_graphs_with_more_vertex_faults","222331089_Edge-bipancyclicity_and_edge-fault-tolerant_bipancyclicity_of_bubble-sort_graphs","220329229_A_Group-Theoretic_Model_for_Symmetric_Interconnection_Networks","220318151_A_note_on_edge_fault_tolerance_with_respect_to_hypercubes","220313758_Improving_bounds_on_link_failure_tolerance_of_the_star_graph","220313683_Vertex-disjoint_spanning_trees_of_the_star_network_with_applications_to_fault-tolerance_and_security","220313572_Robustness_of_star_graph_network_under_link_failure","220150872_Fault-tolerant_embedding_of_paths_in_crossed_cubes","220150548_Fault-free_longest_paths_in_star_networks_with_conditional_link_faults","220148908_Fault-free_Hamiltonian_cycles_in_twisted_cubes_with_conditional_link_faults","220111479_A_study_of_fault_tolerance_in_star_graph","4061281_Node-to-node_internally_disjoint_paths_problem_in_bubble-sort_graphs"]}